## 7. Error Handling Rules

### 7.1 Never handle errors in routes or controllers

All errors bubble up to `error.plugin.ts` automatically.
Do not wrap service calls in try/catch in controllers.

### 7.3 Create error classes by extending `AppError`

Create Error based on requirement by extending `AppError` in `<feature>.error.ts`

```ts
export class TaskNotFoundError extends ApplicationError {
  constructor(message?: string, metadata?: unknown, error: Error) {
    super({
      message,
      metadata,
      cause: error;
      statusCode: 404,
      logType: LogType.WARN,
    });
  }
}
```

