## 12. API Response Rules

### 12.1 Always use response helper functions

Never construct response objects manually in controllers.
Always import from `@lib/api-response`.

```ts
// ✓ correct
return reply.status(200).send(successResponse(task));
return reply.status(200).send(messageResponse("Email is valid"));
return reply.status(201).send(successResponse(user, "Account created"));

// ✗ wrong — manual response object
return reply.status(200).send({ success: true, data: task });
return reply.status(200).send({ message: "Email is valid", success: true });
```

### 12.2 Standard status codes per operation

- GET one → 200 + successResponse(data)
- GET list → 200 + successResponse(data) or paginatedResponse(data, meta)
- POST create → 201 + successResponse(data, 'Resource created')
- PUT update → 200 + successResponse(data, 'Resource updated')
- DELETE → 204 + no body (reply.status(204).send())
- POST action → 200 + messageResponse('Action description')

### 12.3 Never validate request body manually in controllers

Zod validation happens at the route schema level only.
Never call schema.parse(request.body) in a controller.

```ts
// ✓ correct — validated by Fastify + Zod at route level
validateUserEmail = async (request: FastifyRequest<{ Body: ValidateUserEmailInput }>, reply) => {
  await this.service.validateUserEmail(request.body); // already validated
  return reply.status(200).send(messageResponse("Email is valid"));
};

// ✗ wrong — manual parse in controller
validateUserEmail = async (request, reply) => {
  const body = validateUserEmailSchema.parse(request.body); // remove this
  await this.service.validateUserEmail(body);
};
```

### 12.4 ApiResponse and PaginationMeta types live in packages/shared

Never redefine ApiResponse or PaginationMeta locally in the backend.
Always import from @task-forge/shared and NEVER use the `type` import modifier.

```ts
import { ApiResponse, PaginationMeta } from '@task-forge/shared/types'   ✓
interface ApiResponse { ... }                                      ✗
import type { ApiResponse } from '@task-forge/shared/types'             ✗ — do not use `type`
```

---
